1
00:00:05,699 --> 00:00:08,529
Kṛṣṇa consciousness
is all about

2
00:00:08,529 --> 00:00:13,843
the ultimate loving affectionate 
familiy relationship.

3
00:00:13,843 --> 00:00:17,063
That’s what it is.

4
00:00:17,302 --> 00:00:22,018
Everything else pales in comparison,
is a perverted reflection of that.

5
00:00:22,688 --> 00:00:26,158
[Affection ad Infinitum]

6
00:00:27,254 --> 00:00:31,876
If a child in this world
(we see little cute children),

7
00:00:31,876 --> 00:00:34,239
sometimes they are 
just irresistibly cute—

8
00:00:34,239 --> 00:00:36,092
you can’t take 
your eyes off them,

9
00:00:36,092 --> 00:00:38,192
they make you smile.

10
00:00:38,544 --> 00:00:42,188
How cute do you think 
Kṛṣṇa is, when He is a baby

11
00:00:42,188 --> 00:00:45,148
or a toddler
crawling around?

12
00:00:46,454 --> 00:00:49,122
As cute as the cutest child here

13
00:00:49,122 --> 00:00:56,609
or infinitely more cute, sweet, 
irresistible, and eye-capturing?

14
00:00:56,823 --> 00:00:58,186
I saw a man on the train

15
00:00:58,186 --> 00:01:05,536
when I was going
from New Jersey to JFK,

16
00:01:06,086 --> 00:01:10,484
and this man was on the train
with his little daughter,

17
00:01:10,484 --> 00:01:12,879
she is like four years old, 
maybe

18
00:01:13,549 --> 00:01:15,549
and there was another man
who never met them before.

19
00:01:15,549 --> 00:01:17,825
He was totally enamoured

20
00:01:17,825 --> 00:01:20,468
by the cuteness 
of this four-year-old girl

21
00:01:20,468 --> 00:01:23,814
and practically offering himself
as her slave

22
00:01:23,814 --> 00:01:26,780
after knowing her
for five minutes.

23
00:01:28,490 --> 00:01:31,930
If that’s possible 
in this world

24
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:34,565
do you think 
it might be possible

25
00:01:34,565 --> 00:01:36,595
a similar thing with Kṛṣṇa
 

26
00:01:36,595 --> 00:01:43,735
or the same thing 
magnified ad infinitum?

27
00:01:44,899 --> 00:01:50,499
kandarpa-koṭi-kamanīya-viśeṣa-śobhaṁ
[Bs: 5.30]

28
00:01:52,499 --> 00:01:54,632
Ten million times.

29
00:01:54,632 --> 00:01:56,145
Why only ten million?

30
00:01:56,145 --> 00:01:59,548
Because our brain 
doesn’t work after that.

31
00:02:01,408 --> 00:02:03,958
That’s why they 
are writing the word ‘infinity’

32
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:07,285
or up to this point, then ‘tcht!’.
Then the rest means …

33
00:02:07,285 --> 00:02:13,470
We can’t go: achintya;
kāmārbuda—

34
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:19,255
rasoddāmā kāmārbuda-madhura-dhāmojjvala-tanur
[Śrī Chaianyāṣṭakam: 4]

35
00:02:19,255 --> 00:02:22,300
These sort of descriptions 
were given.

36
00:02:22,995 --> 00:02:25,170
So, understand this principle—

37
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:29,368
whatever you could see 
or have experienced in family life,

38
00:02:29,368 --> 00:02:32,109
then understand,

39
00:02:32,109 --> 00:02:34,244
don’t deny it,

40
00:02:34,244 --> 00:02:35,861
embrace it and understand:

41
00:02:35,861 --> 00:02:42,581
“Oh, so this sort of feeling,
sentiment magnified ad infinitum

42
00:02:42,581 --> 00:02:46,065
starts approaching 
Kṛṣṇa conception.

43
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:52,536
And as my … our good fortune
to come in connection

44
00:02:52,536 --> 00:02:55,328
with lotus feet
of guru and Vaiṣṇav

45
00:02:55,328 --> 00:02:58,229
who are leading us by the hand
in that direction.”

